    <mods:abstract>Trophy, awarded to the winner of the FIFA World Cup between 1930 and 1970. Consists of gold-plated sterling silver statuette of winged female figure holding above her head a decagonal cup, 
        depicting the Goddess Nike. Base replaced in 1954 with lapis lazuli base. Originally called "Victory," it was renamed after FIFA president Jules Rimet. Stolen in 1966 and recovered by
        Pickles the Dog. Stolen again in 1983 and presumed destroyed.
    </mods:abstract> 
